{
  "answer": "In the opening couplet of this ghazal from Ghalib's *Diwan-e-Ghalib*, the poet states that a sigh (*aah*) requires an entire lifetime (*ik umr*) to take effect (*asar hote tak*), rhetorically questioning who could live long enough to untangle the beloved's dark tresses.[^1]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/03-aah-ko-chahiye-ik-umr-asar-hote-tak/translation/#p-0733e9).",
